  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON:  The proposed extension - in particular the front mansard, raised party walls and raised chimney stack and pots - would be clearly visible above the strong parapet line which is a defining feature of the street and the wider East Canonbury Conservation Area.  This level of visibility, both in views from Ockendon Road and longer range views from Essex Road, would cause detriment to the character and appearance of the parent house, the group of houses of which it is a part, the street scene and the wider conservation area.  The proposal therefore conflicts with policy D25 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002), with approved Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) and with PPG15 (particularly paragraph 4.19)."
